      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>capers</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, stirring frequently, or until crisp</p><p>Once crisp, transfer them to a plate, reserving the pan and any remaining oil – these are your <strong>crispy capers</strong></p>",
